claims:
Claims 1. An apparatus, comprising: at least two acoustic sensors through which audio content is received; at least one other sensor; and an audio processor connected to the sensors and configured to receive audio information from the acoustic sensors and other information from the other sensor; wherein the audio processor is configured to determine a use case of the apparatus based on the audio information and the other information; wherein the audio processor is configured to adjust at least one audio processing scheme for the received audio content based on the determined use case. 2. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the audio processor is configured to determine the use case from a plurality of use cases of the apparatus; or wherein the audio processor is configured to determine the use case from a plurality of predetermined use cases of the apparatus. 3. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein each use case has corresponding audio processing parameters, which are selected by adjusting the at least one audio processing scheme based on the determined use case. 4. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the at least one audio processing scheme is configured to select a set of audio parameters from a set of predetermined audio parameters by adjusting the at least one audio scheme. 5. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the use case is determined based on an activity class of the apparatus. 6. The apparatus of claim 5, wherein the use case is further determined based on an orientation of the apparatus; or wherein the use case is further determined based on information about a surface against which the apparatus is positioned. 7. The apparatus of claim 5, wherein the activity class defines an approximation of a current activity or movement of the apparatus or a current activity or movement of user of the apparatus; or wherein the activity class is based on the other information received from the other sensor. 8. The apparatus of claim 5, wherein the activity class is configured to be automatically determined based on a closest approximate of an activity, which the user of the apparatus is doing; or 

 wherein the audio processor is configured to receive the use case or the activity class from an application, which is configured to determine the use case or the activity class; or wherein the audio processor is configured to determine the activity class among a plurality of predetermined activity classes. 9. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the audio processor is configured to determine the use case based on a quality of a surface on which the apparatus is located, and wherein the quality of the surface is determined from the audio information or from the other information or from a combination of these. 10. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the audio sensor includes a microphone and the other sensor comprises at least one of: a magnetometer, a light sensor, a gyroscope, a hygrometer, a thermometer, a barometer, a proximeter, an accelerometer, or an ultrasonic transducer. 11. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the at least one audio algorithm is configured to adjust at least one of: beamforming, an adaptive interference canceller, or a calibration scheme. 12. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the audio processor is configured to adjust the at least one audio processing scheme for a main beam configuration or for an anti beam configuration of the acoustic sensors based on the determined use case. 13. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the audio processor is configured to adjust the at least one audio processing scheme so as to adjust sensitivity difference estimation between acoustic sensors based on the determined use case. 14. A computer-readable storage medium comprising executable instructions for causing at least one processor of a computing apparatus to perform operations comprising: receive audio information from at least two acoustic sensors; receive other information from at least one other sensor; receive, by an audio processor connected to the sensors, the audio information and the other information; determine, by the audio processor, a use case of the apparatus based on the audio information and the other information; and adjust, by the audio processor, at least one audio processing scheme for the received audio information based on the determined use case. 15. A method, comprising: receiving audio content from at least two acoustic sensors; 

 receiving other information from at least one other sensor; determining a use case of an apparatus based on the audio content and the other information; and adjusting at least one audio processing scheme for the received audio content based on the determined use case.
